BENNETT REALTY COMPANY ET AL., PROSECUTORS, v. MAYOR AND ALDERMEN OF JERSEY CITY ET AL., DEFENDANTS. Argued January 18, 1928 Decided May 1, 1928.

Before Justices Parker, Minturn and Campbell.

For the prosecutors, Warren Dixon. For the defendants, Thomas J. Brogan and Frank J. Reardon. Per Curiam.

This ease is controlled by our decision in Kelly v. Jersey City, number 296 of the present term, and for the reasons stated in the per curiam of this court in that case, the confirmation of-the assessment in the present case will be set aside.
